topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sony to balance melees again</span><hr size=1> PoP has made hybrid classes and casters  much stronger than previous expansions where rogues ruled kunark and monks stepped up in Velious and Luclin.<br>
<br>
As guilds progress through PoP, they will run into tons of pal/sk weapons (at least 15-20 I can remember off the top of my head).  With the addition of more vengeance gear and their spells, hybrids can easily sustain 100-120 dps.  High end knights near the 250 attack cap are capable of 130-150 dps.  I've parsed Meulgy and his blade of war ( when he's not AFK for 5 hours) doing 140 dps when he's not 2/3 boxing.<br>
<br>
&lt;I&gt;Unbuffed monks (with epic) in POP can get upwards of 200dps&lt;/I&gt;<br>
<br>
There's no way in hell an unbuffed epic monk, even decked out in Time gear, will do 200 sustained dps on Luclin mobs.  There's no way you'd see this type of sustained dps on low ac PoP mobs.  High end monks currently are doing 170-200 dps fully buffed in PoP.<br>
<br>
&lt;I&gt;I dunno man. I've parsed a lot of warriors and I have yet to see ANY warrior break 110dps in pure melee. &lt;/I&gt;<br>
<br>
it all depends on the weapons they use and their AAs.  A Luclin equipped warrior with most of their offensive AAs using something like Bloodfrenzy/Hategiver/Blade of Carnage combo will do approx 110-120 dps on PoP mobs... but duel wield currently is not the ideal setup for dps.. 2hs PoP weapons are the way to go.  A non tanking warrior with an ornate greatblade (common drop off Druav in PoFire) can do 130-140+ dps.  Supposedly Time equipped warriors are doing 170-180 dps, which I find feasible.  A high end warrior using something like edge of eternity, ivory hilted cleaver, ethereal destroyer, etc.. can sustain 140+ dps duel wielding but with the ripostes in PoP, duel wielding isn't usually the best choice.<br>
<br>
&lt;I&gt;Rogues and monks are OFTEN neck and neck for melee DPS in raid parses&lt;/I&gt;<br>
<br>
Velious and Luclin offered a decent amount of weapon selections for monks while the rogue weapons were a bit sparse.  Compare equally equipped rogue and monk and the rogue will blow the monk away on most situations.<br>
<br>
Warrior class has long been broken.  You can put a high end warrior up against a bazaar equipped Pally and the pally could steal aggro just pissing on the mob. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362635" target="top">Derrict Thealcoholic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.namelesstavern.com" target="top"> Nameless Server</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
