<br>
I noticed that mobs in BOT tend to parry/riposte a bit more than in other zones, but still have low AC.  This definitely could have been the reason for never seeing warriors break 110dps and averaging around 90dps.<br>
<br>
Regarding the comment about monks being capable of hitting 200dps unbuffed (with epic), this was based on parses of monks in the arena while they fought a mage pet.  I parsed a few monks and they varied between 170 and 202dps against the epic pet.  I parsed several other classes v/s the same pet and warriors were by far the lowest.  Knight classes were lower than warriors when their spells were removed from the equation.<br>
<br>
I think that hybrids could use a small boost in melee power but not as much as others.  Warriors, monks, rogues, and rangers are probably the real focus of this tuning so I'm just hoping that maybe folks will get some ideas from this thread and /feedback them to sony BEFORE they make their decision on what to do.<br>
<br>
I'd like to point out that SONY intends to make some balancing changes. If they're going to make changes anyway, I hope we can persuade them not to make the game easier.  I play this game for the challenge and coordination of teamwork.  If they remove the challenge by turning all the PCs into gods, I can't seem much point in playing.<br>
<br>
