</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
a lot depends on their AA, if they don't have stalwart endurance, they'll be stunned often.  If they don't have tactical mastery, they won't be hitting through the mob dodge/parry/ripostes.  Those 2 AAs alone can account for the difference.<br>
<br>
You also have to remember most warriors in BoT are using epic, fleshgrinders, or whatever.  You'll run into a few with BoC or other types of 15-20ish weapons but the majority aren't using high dps type weapons.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Regarding the comment about monks being capable of hitting 200dps unbuffed (with epic), this was based on parses of monks in the arena while they fought a mage pet</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
pets have pretty much no ac mitigation.  Give me a pally to tank an epic mage pet and I'd smack it for 270-300+ sustained dps with just SoV.<br>
<br>
Hybrids, as they are, are fine.  PoP already has an overabundance of knight items.  PoP is the best expansion knights have ever seen... they're are pretty much capable of being within several hundred HP of a warrior, the main difference coming from their base HP.  Warriors are still defined by their evasive and defensive disciplines (and AE taunt) but for everything else where those aren't needed, knight &gt; warrior.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Warriors, monks, rogues, and rangers are probably the real focus of this tuning </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
rangers are fine, all the hybrids are fine.  Just the pure melee need tuning. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=riddek>Riddek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#333333>(7/23/03 8:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9940.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sony to balance melees again</span><hr size=1> I have allways prefered dual wielding, Using a blade of carnage in my primary ( part of my highest agro combination) I generally hover around 130 dps.<br>
